  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Advocacy and alliances for Disaster Risk Reduction management in Guatemala</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This proposal seeks to promote the use of online social networks most commonly used in Guatemala (facebook, twitter, etc..) In order to strengthen the coordination between the platform Metropolitan COLRED, ECORED, civil society actors 8 municipalities Guatemala department through the training of 60 young people from different communities highly vulnerable to disasters. In late October 2013, young people trained in social networks will be in the ability to connect to the media and disaster response system in the country for both exposing the needs of urban communities which are affected by disasters.</narrative>
  </description>
